title: Grateful Dead Live at Rainbow Theater on 1981-10-04
description:
Set 1

Jam-> Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil-> El Paso, Jack A Roe, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women-> Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Let It Grow-> Deal

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow-> Samson & Delilah, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: . dude, separating scarlet/fire with a 'jam' track!!! why in the world would you do that??
Smokin' Show The boys were on fire!!!  Stellar show and very together.  Definitely one of the top favorites, grateful for this board.

About a 3.5 I dunno. Some people like fast guitar playing no matter how sloppy it is. I don't like sloppy playing no matter how fast it is. On fire? Maybe that's not always a good thing. Being a little cooler and more fluid is good too.
